1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,273
Hello, I am the owner who lives with my Jindo dog, Hongsi. Today, I will share how my Hongsi and our neighbors can be happy together.

2
00:00:09,273 --> 00:00:14,709
My Hongsi is a beautiful female Jindo dog, black-furred with sparse white patches scattered throughout.

3
00:00:14,709 --> 00:00:23,045
When Hongsi was hurt fighting a badger on a mountain trail recently, I held her all night crying and nursing her. That night, we truly became family.

4
00:00:23,045 --> 00:00:29,809
Yet when a neighbor flinches and steps back upon seeing Hongsi in the elevator, a corner of my heart aches.

5
00:00:29,809 --> 00:00:37,682
I cannot blame them. To someone bitten by a dog before, a large dog can feel like pure fear itself.

6
00:00:37,682 --> 00:00:44,427
Moreover, irresponsible owners who unleash their dogs or leave waste behind deepen the conflict even further.

7
00:00:44,427 --> 00:00:50,709
So, for Hongsi and for our neighbors, I made up my mind to become a responsible guardian.

8
00:00:50,709 --> 00:00:57,627
In Germany, a dog tax called Hundesteuer is collected and reinvested into clean parks and waste-bag stations.

9
00:00:57,627 --> 00:01:04,327
The tax is not a burden but a warm promise, society sharing the responsibility of living alongside dogs.

10
00:01:04,327 --> 00:01:10,500
In Japan, separate dog-run areas and walking zones are designated so dogs have their own space to play.

11
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:17,173
Within the designated areas Hongsi runs freely, while outside them neighbors can pass by at ease.

12
00:01:17,173 --> 00:01:23,082
In one apartment, an elevator now has a button that signals a dog is on board.

13
00:01:23,082 --> 00:01:29,282
Pressing it lets waiting neighbors know in advance, greatly reducing surprises and unwanted encounters.

14
00:01:29,282 --> 00:01:35,327
In our neighborhood, owners gathered and started a community training group for dog socialization.

15
00:01:35,327 --> 00:01:41,982
Hongsi learned to sit and wait, while I grew together with other owners by sharing know-how.

16
00:01:41,982 --> 00:01:48,727
Now, in the elevator, I hold the leash short within two meters and keep Hongsi close beside my leg.

17
00:01:48,727 --> 00:01:54,945
On days she is shy around people, I tie a yellow ribbon to signal that we need some distance today.

18
00:01:54,945 --> 00:02:01,036
Neighbors, too, show respect, not touching or shouting without consent, and taking a step back.

19
00:02:01,036 --> 00:02:08,109
Always carrying waste bags and cleaning up every trace, these small habits build everyone's trust.

20
00:02:08,109 --> 00:02:16,245
As care builds little by little, people and Hongsi alike become safe, warm neighbors. Please love my Hongsi.
